text: Prolixicheilus longisulcus is a species of fish in the family Cyprinidae, found in streams belonging to the Zuojiang River, a tributary of Pearl River in China. This species is the only member of its genus. ==References== Category:Labeoninae Category:Monotypic ray-finned fish genera Category:Cyprinidae genera Category:Cyprinid fish of Asia Category:Fish of China
